post_text:
Update on Masks
Last week, Governor Holcomb gave an executive order mandating masks for the entire state of Indiana. His guidelines were for people 8 years and older.
In light of the Governor’s order and age guidelines, the Starke County Health Department has amended the Face Covering Mandate for our County. The entire amendment can be found at http://www.co.starke.in.us/health/MASK%20MANDATE%207-27-20.pdf. Section A. 1 speaks specifically to K-12 Educational Institutions. We are grateful for this amendment, as it offers a realistic attempt in having students wear masks.
Our stance on this is: Grades K-2 are strongly encouraged to wear face coverings, but not mandated. Grades 3-12 remain in the category of “settled and spaced” as previously stated in our NJ-SP stance on masks. We appreciate the Starke County Health Department working with the schools on being better able to comply with orders.

Annette Zupin, Ph.D.
Superintendent
North Judson-San Pierre School Corporation

post_text:
Important Information regarding Kindergarten Countdown and Supply Lists

Kindergarten Countdown- The Kindergarten Countdown program will proceed starting Aug 3. Information specific to those parents will be sent via school messenger. Please plan for students to be contacted by the bus driver as to exact pick up times. The driver will call each parent(s) to share that information. Students may be dropped off and picked up if a parent prefers. It will run Monday, August 3rd to Thursday, August 6th. You may contact the office starting on July 27 for more information.

Supply Lists-
Supply lists for grades K-6 will be posted on July 27. They are similar to last year, however, due to the Covid situation some modifications have been made and continue to change. 6th graders will not have use of lockers to start the year.

post_text: We salute NJ-SP Elementary Art & Computer Teacher Mrs. Dumas and thank her for 21 years of service (Kindergarten-6th Grade)! Mrs. Dumas reflected,”Teaching Art to elementary students was so fun and rewarding. My students were always interested in learning about artists, art styles, and techniques in art, and were enthusiastic in their artistic expression. I always loved seeing them use their creativity to make art that was unique to them. I had the best job, in the best room in the school!” Mrs. Dumas is in the process of moving to Indianapolis to be closer to family, spend more time with her granddaughters, and continue to create art! Congratulations and best wishes!

post_text:
North Judson-San Pierre to Begin Serving Hot Lunches

Beginning May 4, North Judson-San Pierre School Corporation will change their current lunch serving program. The change comes about in order to meet supply and demand as well as offer a different variety of meal.

From May 4 through May 22 all lunches will be served from the Jr-Sr High School front parking lot. All lunches will be hot lunches. Parents will be permitted to pick up the hot meals without their children present. However, the students’ ID number must be given in order to meet federal compliance rules.

Because NJ-SP is registered as an “open” site, any child in the community may come, regardless of whether or not they are students in our corporation.
text:
North Judson-San Pierre to Begin Serving Hot Lunches

Beginning May 4, North Judson-San Pierre School Corporation will change their current lunch serving program. The change comes about in order to meet supply and demand as well as offer a different variety of meal.

From May 4 through May 22 all lunches will be served from the Jr-Sr High School front parking lot. All lunches will be hot lunches. Parents will be permitted to pick up the hot meals without their children present. However, the students’ ID number must be given in order to meet federal compliance rules.

Because NJ-SP is registered as an “open” site, any child in the community may come, regardless of whether or not they are students in our corporation.

post_text:
The response and participation in our lunch program has been very positive. We want everyone to continue to use the lunch program and encourage others to do so as well. We will be increasing the number of lunches provided at each site, as we have run out the past couple of days. We will also be reevaluating our distribution areas to see if there are better ways to serve the lunches. More information will come in the next several days regarding changes to serving lunches. For now, we will increase the number of lunches we make and the sites and time will remain the same. Thank you for your support and patience as we work through this time together to meet the needs of our students and community.
Dr. Zupin

post_text: If you haven’t completed 2020 Census information, the Census Bureau will be mailing a questionnaire to your attention. Individuals can also complete the census online at my2020census.gov or you can respond via phone, by calling (844) 330-2020. The 2020 Census count impacts the federal funds that communities receive each year for programs and services that are critical for schools, students, and younger children. Your cooperation and participation in the 2020 Census helps our schools.

Did you know how the 2020 Census affects children?… The 2020 Census count impacts the federal funds that communities receive each year for programs and services that are critical for schools, students, and younger children, such as:
• Special education, Head Start, after-school programs,
and classroom technology.
• Food assistance, including free and reduced-price school lunches.
• Maternal and child health programs.
Your cooperation and participation means so much to our country and to our children.

North Judson-San Pierre School Corporation has been closely following recent media reports and information from The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) about Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19). Our school nurse and staff are working with students to promote good hygiene and to keep everyone healthy and safe. We have also worked with our custodial workers to ensure our schools receive thorough cleaning every day.

We will continue to follow the guidance from the DOE and CDC. Parents are asked for help in reinforcing healthy practices at home with children.

post_text: NJ-SP Class of 2020 Senior Spotlight: Ashton Chole Kennedy-What are your plans after graduation?…"I’m going to be attending Valparaiso University next year and pursuing a degree in nursing. I received an Honors Scholarship and a Valpo Fund Alumni Award from the college itself. I also have a 21st Century Scholarship & Award, a Valpo 21st Century Award, and I’m still applying to many more! I was directly admitted into the nursing program and after graduating I am hoping to work in Geriatrics, as an ER nurse, or in pediatrics” Best of luck Ashton!-from all of us at NJ-SP Schools.

post_text: In third grade this week we have been learning about biographies. The students read a biography about James Naismith, the man who invented basketball. In addition to learning the history of basketball, the students learned more about the game, hard work, and the importance of a good education from our very own Indiana Basketball Hall of Fame member and sixth grade teacher Deb Bolen! Three cheers for basketball history, Ms. Bolen, and learning!
